Program: The History Hour
Title: First CIA coup in Latin America
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0429lfz
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 1 Aug 2016
In this week's programme, we hear personal accounts of two fronts in America's Cold War fight against communism: Guatemala and Russia itself. Plus, the earthquake in China that killed a quarter of a million; riots in the English city of Liverpool; and remembering Picasso in his prime. PHOTO: Army officers opposed to President Arbenz go over a map of the territory on their push to Zacapa and then to Guatemala City, July 1954. (AP Photo) Show less